    "description": "If you're a passionate Risk Analyst with drive and ambition, KPMG India International Enterprises in Aurangabad is the place for you. We're growing fast and need talented people to grow with us.\n\nAbout KPMG India International Enterprises:\nKPMG India International Enterprises is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Prepare and analyze financial statements, reports, and budgets\n• Monitor financial performance against targets and provide variance analysis\n• Prepare MIS reports for senior management review\n• Manage accounts payable and accounts receivable functions\n• Implement and maintain internal controls and audit procedures\n• Coordinate with external auditors during annual audits\n• Conduct due diligence for mergers, acquisitions, and investments\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Diploma or Degree in Hospitality Management\n• 3-6 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Forecasting\n• Proficiency in SAP FICO\n• Proficiency in Financial Modeling\n• Proficiency in VBA\n• Proficiency in Due Diligence\n• Proficiency in Budgeting\n• Proficiency in IFRS\n• Proficiency in Financial Reporting\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Life and accident insurance\n• Meal coupons and food allowance\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Salary Range: 7 LPA - 15 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Aurangabad, Maharashtra, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with KPMG India International Enterprises!",
